<TITLE> Channel 1 appeals against station closure </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 2 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court has agreed to hear a writ petition filed by the private television channel Channel 1 challenging the legality of the decision to suspend its transmission. The High Court bench of justices Syed Mahmud Hossain and Gobinda Chandra Thakur said it would hear the petition following an application by the channel. Channel 1 director Mazidul Islam filed the appeal on behalf of the TV station. Advocate Ahsanul Karim said the hearing might take place later in the day. The TV station was taken off air on Apr 27 by the regulators alleging that the station had broken the law The station started transmission on Jan 24, 2006 during the regime of the BNP-led government. bd
